A vintage 1960s-style technical illustration of an enormous filing cabinet stretching impossibly tall into a sepia-toned sky, with hundreds of tiny drawers slightly ajar. Small mechanical brass gears and clockwork mechanisms connect the drawers in intricate patterns, suggesting automated sorting. A single magnifying glass on a brass stand focuses on one particular drawer in the middle, casting a warm golden spotlight. The aesthetic combines Victorian industrial design with mid-century office equipment, rendered in muted browns, creams, and touches of amber. Paper documents with abstract patterns (no readable text) flutter gently between drawer levels like autumn leaves. The perspective is dramatic, looking upward from ground level, emphasizing the overwhelming scale of organized data management.
